text: William Tritschler (July 19, 1873 - July 13, 1939) was an American gymnast. He competed in four events at the 1904 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1873 births Category:1939 deaths Category:American male artistic gymnasts Category:Olympic gymnasts of the United States Category:Gymnasts at the 1904 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from St. Louis
